{
  "document_id": "job-38",
  "title": "Job 38",
  "type": "scripture",
  "translation": "NRSVue",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "block_id": "job-38-heading-the-lord-answers-job",
      "type": "heading",
      "text": "The Lord Answers Job"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-38-1",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 1,
      "text": "Then the Lord answered Job out of the whirlwind:"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-38-2",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 2,
      "text": "“Who is this that darkens counsel by words without knowledge?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-38-3",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 3,
      "text": "Gird up your loins like a man;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-38-4",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 4,
      "text": "“Where were you when I laid the foundation of the earth?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-38-5",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 5,
      "text": "Who determined its measurements—surely you know!"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-38-6",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 6,
      "text": "On what were its bases sunk,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-38-7",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 7,
      "text": "when the morning stars sang together"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-38-8",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 8,
      "text": "“Or who shut in the sea with doors"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-38-9",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 9,
      "text": "when I made the clouds its garment"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-38-10",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 10,
      "text": "and prescribed bounds for it,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-38-11",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 11,
      "text": "and said, ‘Thus far shall you come and no farther,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-38-12",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 12,
      "text": "“Have you commanded the morning since your days began"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-38-13",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 13,
      "text": "so that it might take hold of the skirts of the earth,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-38-14",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 14,
      "text": "It is changed like clay under the seal,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-38-15",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 15,
      "text": "Light is withheld from the wicked,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-38-16",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 16,
      "text": "“Have you entered into the springs of the sea"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-38-17",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 17,
      "text": "Have the gates of death been revealed to you,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-38-18",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 18,
      "text": "Have you comprehended the expanse of the earth?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-38-19",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 19,
      "text": "“Where is the way to the dwelling of light,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-38-20",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 20,
      "text": "that you may take it to its territory"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-38-21",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 21,
      "text": "Surely you know, for you were born then,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-38-22",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 22,
      "text": "“Have you entered the storehouses of the snow,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-38-23",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 23,
      "text": "which I have reserved for the time of trouble,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-38-24",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 24,
      "text": "What is the way to the place where the light is distributed"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-38-25",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 25,
      "text": "“Who has cut a channel for the torrents of rain"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-38-26",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 26,
      "text": "to bring rain on a land where no one lives,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-38-27",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 27,
      "text": "to satisfy the waste and desolate land,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-38-28",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 28,
      "text": "“Has the rain a father,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-38-29",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 29,
      "text": "From whose womb did the ice come forth,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-38-30",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 30,
      "text": "The waters become hard like stone,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-38-31",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 31,
      "text": "“Can you bind the chains of the Pleiades"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-38-32",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 32,
      "text": "Can you lead forth the Mazzaroth in their season,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-38-33",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 33,
      "text": "Do you know the ordinances of the heavens?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-38-34",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 34,
      "text": "“Can you lift up your voice to the clouds,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-38-35",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 35,
      "text": "Can you send forth lightnings, so that they may go"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-38-36",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 36,
      "text": "Who has put wisdom in the inward parts"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-38-37",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 37,
      "text": "Who has the wisdom to number the clouds?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-38-38",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 38,
      "text": "when the dust runs into a mass"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-38-39",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 39,
      "text": "“Can you hunt the prey for the lion"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-38-40",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 40,
      "text": "when they crouch in their dens"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-38-41",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 41,
      "text": "Who provides for the raven its prey,"
    }
  ]
}